<p style="text-align:justify;">and some are Copies of Originals which are not to be found <span class="AddHand-author">&amp; almost all in confusion.</span>  The Written Paper of M<sup>r</sup> Panet which should be on record, is not endorsed "<span style="text-decoration:underline;">filed</span>"; It has only the Initials of M<sup>r</sup> Lynd; if <span class="DelHand-author">that</span> <span class="AddHand-author">those </span>mean that it was regularly <span style="text-decoration:underline;">filed</span>, it cannot be interp<span class="AddHand-author">r</span>eted to certify that it was <span style="text-decoration:underline;">read</span> <span class="AddHand-author">or</span> <span class="AddHand-author">that he was heard in argument; </span>it exhibits no proof of <span class="DelHand-author">being read</span> <span class="AddHand-author">either</span>.  It is the Law of all Countries that the Records of a Court be kept in regular order &amp; method; Make your election of English or French Law, or both; they command regularity order and Method in your Records.  It remains with you to prove the existence of order &amp; Method, <span class="AddHand-author">before any degree of Credit can be given to them. </span><span class="DelHand-author">that all papers filed may have the authenticity of Records</span>.  I presume you do not mean to refer to the <span style="text-decoration:underline;">Cut</span> and <span style="text-decoration:underline;">Dry</span> &#173; Judgement, as the Record of the Court, to prove that M<sup>r</sup> Panets written Paper was <span style="text-decoration:underline;">read</span> &amp; <span style="text-decoration:underline;">filed</span> <span class="AddHand-author">or that he was heard in Argument</span>; for though you may have therein <span style="text-decoration:underline;">premised</span> <span class="AddHand-author">that he was heard or </span>that it was <span style="text-decoration:underline;">read</span>, very little Credit will be given to an instrument laboring under so unfavorable a complexion, an instrument made out before you came into Court, <span class="DelHand-author">and therefore <span style="text-decoration:underline;">read</span> and <span style="text-decoration:underline;">filed</span> was</span> <span class="AddHand-author">and in which therefore </span><span class="AddHand-author"><span style="text-decoration:underline;">read</span></span><span class="AddHand-author"> &amp; </span><span class="AddHand-author"><span style="text-decoration:underline;">filed</span></span><span class="AddHand-author"> or <span class="DelHand-author">heard</span> must have been</span> inserted <span class="DelHand-author">on it</span> before you heard the Defense <span style="text-decoration:underline;">read</span> <span class="AddHand-author">&amp; before you ordered it to be </span><span style="text-decoration:underline;">filed</span>; Perhaps you intended it should be read; it is a misfortune you did not adhere to your intention; it was not <span style="text-decoration:underline;">read</span>, <span class="AddHand-author">nor was he heard </span>and to file a paper without <span class="AddHand-author">hearing the advocate in argument or without </span>reading it, is (with respect to the immediate Subject before the Court) much the </p>

